{
  "texts": [
    "A key aspect is whether we wish to enable symmetries of Ĥ to be broken.",
    "If P 0 respects a particular symmetry of Ĥ, then that symmetry will be preserved in the HF Hamiltonian H HF [P 0] and hence future iterations.",
    "3.3, we will discuss how to handle symmetries in the context of TBG.",
    "For now, we consider unrestricted HF calculations with no restriction on the symmetry of the variational state (apart from particle-number conservation).The most common application of HF is to study the mean-field phase diagram.",
    "While the main goal is to obtain the variational ground state, understanding the competing states (which may be local but not global energy minima) is also useful."
  ]
